    <string name="donate_tier_sponsors_blurb">Monthly sponsorship, processed by GitHub. Lowest fees, no platform cut. The most stable way to support Dish month after month, and the only one that GitHub matches dollar-for-dollar through the GitHub Sponsors Matching Fund where eligible.</string>
    <string name="donate_tier_sponsors_currencies">Card, PayPal, GitHub credit</string>
    <string name="donate_tier_kofi_blurb">Tip jar. Buy us a coffee, no account required. Ko-fi takes no cut on one-time tips, so every dollar reaches the project.</string>
    <string name="donate_tier_kofi_currencies">Card, Apple Pay, Google Pay, PayPal</string>
    <string name="donate_tier_bmac_blurb">Quick one-time gift or a monthly membership. Card, Apple Pay, or Google Pay. Great if you don\'t have a GitHub account.</string>
    <string name="donate_tier_bmac_currencies">Card, Apple Pay, Google Pay</string>

    <string name="donate_why_title">What your donation pays for</string>
    <string name="donate_why_hosting">Hosting. dish.tinkernorth.com, tinkernorth.com, and every signed-installer mirror. AWS isn\'t free, even at our traffic scale.</string>
    <string name="donate_why_signing">Code-signing certificates. Windows SmartScreen only plays nice because we pay for an EV certificate every year. The same goes for the Apple Developer Program account for the upcoming macOS client.</string>
    <string name="donate_why_play">Google Play developer fee. A one-time $25 fee plus the time required to keep the Play listing compliant with every new policy round.</string>
    <string name="donate_why_time">Time. Honest answer: most of it. Dish is a nights-and-weekends project. Donations let me say \"yes\" to working on it instead of taking on extra consulting.</string>

    <string name="donate_thanks">Thank you. Every dollar, every star, every shared link. They all add up. Emir</string>

